  Officer of Second Age <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulangevin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Langevin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/10/01 3:24:58 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frontier Mountain Cycles, Med Totem (SPOILERS)</span><hr size=1> I know this is old.. but being a self-proclaimed expert on these cycles, I figured i'd add this since some people were asking.<br>
<br>
You can solo the cycle at 44 (druid).  The only problem is that the Overseer has a lot of HP, and you may end up resorting to med/kiting (which, IMO sucks and is a last resort tactic).  Also, if you plan to do the sarnak cycle before 49 (not recommended), you'll have trouble with some of them, since they are healers.  Even the cenobyte can be a problem, since druids don't really have reliable stuns (before Velious, really none).<br>
<br>
The best time to really hammer out farming the cycles is 52, when you get breath of ro.  Then you can knock out the Overseer in on time.<br>
<br>
The hardest part about the &quot;bug&quot; of split spawns (multiple spawns per cycle), is that since the giants share spots in both cycles, you might end up with 3 Overseers and not know which one is for your particular cycle.  This is highly annoying when you're sub 50 and killing him takes a good amount of effort.<br>
<br>
<br>
The best thing to do, is bind in the spawn spot where the item is you wish to get.  Since it's usually the totem, bind just in front of the pointed mountain, in between it and the DL zone.  The longest run is from NW to the DL corner anyhow, so binding near DL makes the most sense, since you need to get back ASAP.  Oh, and don't kill the mole with little mana in reserve, or you won't have anything left for Blug.  Blug is a wizard, and very weak.  A starfire and another nuke are enough to take him down.<br>
<br>
It's a bit harder to do this now.. before FM was virtually empty and it was great to have the zone to yourself.. Nowadays, it's not so easy, and you're likely to be stepping on someone else's turf.<br>
<br>
Have fun!<br>
<br>
